  "prompt": "What are the best online shopping aggregators? For deals, comparisons, etc.",
  "response": "Okay, here's a breakdown of some of the best online shopping aggregators, categorized by their strengths:\n\n**1. Comprehensive Product Search & Price Comparison:**\n\n*   **Google Shopping:**  (shopping.google.com)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Massive product database, integrates directly with Google search, detailed product information, price history charts, merchant reviews.  Excellent for finding the absolute lowest price on a specific item.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Can feel overwhelming with so many options, results can be influenced by paid placement (though generally clearly marked).  Not as strong for *discovering* deals you weren't already looking for.\n*   **Bing Shopping:** (bing.com/shop)\n    *   **Strengths:** Similar to Google Shopping, utilizes Bing's search technology. Offers price comparison, product reviews, and often cashback rewards through Microsoft Rewards.\n    *   **Weaknesses:** Smaller product selection than Google Shopping, Interface not as intuitive for some users.\n*   **PriceRunner:** (pricerunner.com)\n    *   **Strengths:** A dedicated price comparison site that has been around for a long time.  Strong emphasis on independent price tracking and offers detailed product specifications.\n    *   **Weaknesses:** Can be less visually appealing than some modern aggregators.  Less well-known than Google Shopping, so may miss some retailers.\n\n**2. Deal Aggregators & Curated Shopping Experiences:**\n\n*   **DealNews:** (dealnews.com)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Hand-picked deals from a variety of retailers.  Editorial team curates the best offers, making it easier to find quality deals.  Good for finding discounts on electronics, apparel, and home goods.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Focus is on deals, not necessarily comprehensive price comparison for every product.  Can be ad-heavy.\n*   **Slickdeals:** (slickdeals.net)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Community-driven deal site.  Users post and vote on deals, so the best offers rise to the top.  Very active forum for discussing deals and getting advice.  Great for finding hidden gems and \"stacking\" deals.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Quality of deals can vary depending on the community's finds.  Requires more active participation to find the best offers. Can be overwhelming at times.\n*   **RetailMeNot:** (retailmenot.com)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Focuses on coupons, promo codes, and cashback offers.  Good for saving money on specific purchases.  Browser extension can automatically find and apply coupons.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Less about comprehensive product search, more about finding discounts for retailers you already know.\n\n**3. Visual Discovery & Inspiration:**\n\n*   **Pinterest:** (pinterest.com)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Excellent for discovering products you weren't necessarily looking for.  Visual search helps you find items based on images.  Great for home decor, fashion, and DIY projects.  Increasingly linking directly to product pages.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Less precise for specific price comparison.  Can be distracting with non-shopping content.\n*   **Wanelo:** (wanelo.co)\n    *   **Strengths:** A social shopping platform where users can discover and save products from various online stores. Good for finding unique and trendy items.\n    *   **Weaknesses:** Can be overwhelming with a large number of products.\n*   **Etsy:** (etsy.com)\n   *   **Strengths:** Perfect for handmade, vintage, and unique items.  Excellent for finding personalized gifts and supporting independent creators.\n   *   **Weaknesses:** Prices may be higher than mass-produced items.  Shipping times can vary.\n\n**4. Cashback & Rewards Programs:**\n\n*   **Rakuten (formerly Ebates):** (rakuten.com)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Earn cashback on purchases at a wide range of retailers.  Simple to use. Browser extension reminds you to activate cashback.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Cashback rates can vary.  Requires you to start your shopping trip through the Rakuten portal or extension.\n*   **Honey:** (joinhoney.com)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Automatically finds and applies coupon codes at checkout.  Also offers cashback rewards.  Owned by PayPal.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Cashback rates may not be as high as some dedicated cashback sites.\n*   **Capital One Shopping:** (capitaloneshopping.com)\n    *   **Strengths:**  Automatically finds and applies coupon codes, compares prices, and offers rewards.\n    *   **Weaknesses:** Primarily benefits Capital One cardholders for maximum rewards.\n\n**5. Niche Aggregators:**\n\n*   **CamelCamelCamel:** (camelcamelcamel.com) - **Amazon Price Tracker**\n    *   **Strengths:** Tracks the price history of products on Amazon.  You can set up price alerts to be notified when the price drops.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Limited to Amazon.\n*   **Lyst:** (lyst.com) - **Fashion Aggregator**\n    *   **Strengths:**  Aggregates fashion products from a wide range of retailers.  Allows you to create wishlists and track prices.\n    *   **Weaknesses:**  Focus is solely on fashion.\n\n**Tips for Using Shopping Aggregators Effectively:**\n\n*   **Be Specific:** The more specific your search terms, the better the results.\n*   **Use Filters:** Most aggregators offer filters for price, brand, color, size, etc. Use these to narrow down your search.\n*   **Read Reviews:**  Check both product reviews and merchant reviews before making a purchase.\n*   **Compare Shipping Costs:**  Factor in shipping costs when comparing prices.\n*   **Check Return Policies:**  Make sure you understand the retailer's return policy before you buy.\n*   **Be Aware of Sponsored Results:**  Pay attention to whether results are organic or sponsored (advertisements).\n*   **Set Price Alerts:**  Use price trackers to be notified when the price of an item drops.\n*   **Combine Strategies:**  Use multiple aggregators and techniques to find the best deals. For example, use Google Shopping to find the lowest price, then check RetailMeNot for coupons.\n\n**Ultimately, the \"best\" aggregator depends on your specific needs and shopping style. Experiment with a few to find the ones that work best for you.** Good luck and happy shopping!\n",
